# Get the canceled bookings for repeated guests (True)
cancelled_bookings = df[df['booking_status'] == 'Canceled'].groupby(df['repeated_guest'] == 1).size()

# Total count of repeated guests (True)
total_repeated_guests = df[df['repeated_guest'] == 1].groupby('repeated_guest').size()

# Calculate percentage
percentage_canceled = (cancelled_bookings / total_repeated_guests) * 100

# Filter out NaN and only get the value for True repeated guests
percentage_canceled = percentage_canceled[True]

# Print the result

In[297]:
#creating a function for metrics evaluation from predicted values
from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score,recall_score,precision_score,f1_score,confusion_matrix,classification_report
def metrics_evaluation(model,predictors,target):
    #predicting values of  data
    y_pred=model.predict(predictors)
    #evaluating metrics
    acc=accuracy_score(target,y_pred)
    rec=recall_score(target,y_pred)
    f1=f1_score(target,y_pred)
    pre=precision_score(target,y_pred)
    metric_df=pd.DataFrame(
        {'accuracy':acc,'recall':rec,'f1_Score':f1,'precision':pre},
        index=[0])
    return metric_df
In[313]:
#creating a function for confusion matrix
def confusion_mat(model,predictors,target):
    y_pred=model.predict(predictors)
    cm=confusion_matrix(target,y_pred)
    labels = np.asarray(
        [
            ["{0:0.0f}".format(item) + "\n{0:.2%}".format(item / cm.flatten().sum())]
            for item in cm.flatten()
        ]
    ).reshape(2, 2)
    plt.figure(figsize=(6,4))
    sns.heatmap(cm,annot=labels,fmt="")
    plt.xlabel('Predicted values')
    plt.ylabel('True values')
    plt.show()

Pruning the Model

In[1]:
#using GridSerachCV for hyperParameter tuning
from sklearn.metrics import make_scorer
from sklearn.model_selection import GridSearchCV
model1=DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42)
parameters = {'max_depth': np.arange(1,10), 
              'min_samples_leaf': [1, 2, 5, 7, 10,15,20],
              'max_leaf_nodes' : [2, 3, 5, 10],
              'min_impurity_decrease': [0.001,0.01,0.1]
             }
# Type of scoring used to compare parameter combinations
f1_scorer = make_scorer(f1_score)

# Type of scoring used to compare parameter combinations
gs=GridSearchCV(model1,parameters,scoring=f1_scorer,cv=5)

#fit the model
gs.fit(X_train,y_train)

# Output the best parameters and score
print("Best Parameters:", gs.best_params_)
print("Best Cross-Validation Score:", gs.best_score_)

In[361]:
# Filter out any invalid (negative or zero) alphas
alphas = alphas[alphas >= 0]

# Training decision trees for each value of alpha
trees = []
for alpha in alphas:
    tree_pruned = DecisionTreeClassifier(random_state=42, ccp_alpha=alpha)
    tree_pruned.fit(X_train, y_train)
    trees.append(tree_pruned)
In[365]:
# Evaluate each model's accuracy on the test set
accuracies = [tree.score(X_test, y_test) for tree in trees]

# Plot the accuracy for each alpha value
plt.plot(alphas, accuracies,drawstyle="steps-post",marker='o')
plt.xlabel('Alpha')
plt.ylabel('Accuracy')
plt.title('Accuracy vs. Alpha for Pruned Trees')
plt.show()

# Calculate F1 scores for each pruned tree using tree predictions
f1_scores = [f1_score(y_test, tree.predict(X_test)) for tree in trees]

# Plot the f1_score for each alpha value
plt.plot(alphas, f1_scores,drawstyle="steps-post",marker='o')
plt.xlabel('Alpha')
plt.ylabel('f1_score')
plt.title('f1_score vs. Alpha for Pruned Trees')
plt.show()
In[368]:
